Here is something I started a while ago. The scale is not correct, because I started this before I realized how HUGE mobile cranes are! This is a Liebherr LTM 1060-3.1 and a Mercedes-Benz Sprinter van (My dream vehicle, besides the LTM 1030-2.1, of course) I will take some better pictures later, and as you can see, it is not finished.

Sorry, for some reason the forum didn't embed the images. If you can't see them, tell me so I can fix it! The drawing is hanging on the hook of my new Lego LTR 1060 telescopic crawler crane. I will post some pictures of that later as well.

Moar art!

A product of mindless Megathread chatter :

Sorry the van is so blocky, but I didn't feel like going through the trouble of adding curved lines. It is meant to be like a Mercedes sprinter van. I may or may not make a better one in the future.

Here is some more stuff (Come on, someone post their art! I don't like double or triple posting.)

I made these back in 2019. There are more, but I am only going to post these for now. I know the wheels are small.

And here is something for all the Futurama fans out there!!

 I drew it on a big piece of paper, then taped it to an old pizza box. I made it around new year's eve of 2020 (I think) To try and recreate the pilot episode of Futurama. If you don't watch Futurama already, you should. It's a great show.

Some stuff I drew 5-7 years ago:

Quote

 


This was some futuristic microcar concept I saw on the internet


Renault, Daihatsu (subsidiary of Toyota), Toyota, Suzuki, Mercedes-Benz, BMW, Chevrolet


Some brand of plasticine (it's real)


The Petronas Twin Towers, plus some other building that I completely made up


A Wankel rotary engine


What little computer knowledge I had back then (I genuinely called the main body 'the CPU', not knowing that a CPU is just one chip out of many)


Some Mazda RX8s

The black splodge was from when I originally intended to fill in the background, never finished it. The more prominent background dots were where I intended for the stars to go in the never-finished background. Ship 2 (left) I've retroactively named UNSC Edwin Hubble NGS-30428 ('NGS' from 'Northrop Grumman Innov. Systems'/Orbital ATK), and Ship 3 (background) is UNSC Johannes Kepler ARS-30429 ('ARS' from 'Arianespace')
